INSERT INTO `activities_tbl` (`id`, `place_id`, `get_there`, `best_time`, `activities`) VALUES
(1, 1, 'From Manila, take a bus bound for Bani or Bolinao in Pangasinan./Drop by the town of Bani, then take a tricycle or jeepney ride to Agno, Pangasinan./There are also direct bus ride  from Manila to Agno, Pangasinan  although it is very limited./The travel time is around 5 to 6 hours. Once in Agno, ride a tricycle that will take you to the Umbrella Rocks.', 'April to May is the best time to visit when it comes to summer vacation.', 'Swimming/Snorkeling/Diving/Camping'),
(2, 2, 'Traveling by bus from Manila to Vigan will be the cheapest option, although expect to spend around 8 to 10 hours on the road. There are many bus lines offering the direct Vigan route, with premium ones such as Partas Bus in Cubao and Farinas Transit in Pasay that feature WiFi, TV, and toilets; and regular bus companies such as Dominion Bus, Aniceto Bus, and Viron Transit at relatively lower fares./Some buses like Philippine Rabbit Bus Line, Florida, Maria de Leon, Baliwag, and RCJ Transit pass by Vigan as well, on their way to Laoag City. It is recommended to take the overnight trips so you can just sleep through the long ride and don’t save on accommodation expenses for one night./If you want to save on time, take a flight from Manila to Laoag, which takes only an hour, and ride a 2-hour bus trip going to Vigan./Once you are in Vigan City, Calle Crisologo is just 500m away from the bus terminal, so take a quick tricycle ride or get there comfortably on foot.', 'The best time to visit Calle Crisologo and other attractions in Vigan City is during the dry season from November to May if you wish to avoid chances of rain and the intense summer heat you can also choose to visit the dry yet colder months of December until February.', 'Tour around the Heritage Village/Shop souvenirs/Food Trip/Ride the Kalesa/Take lots of Selfies and Photos'),
(3, 3, 'To get to Bauang La Union from Manila, take bus(Partas, Florida, Dominion or Farninas) bound for La Union./Fare is approximately PHP 401 and travel time is roughly 4 hours and 30 minutes./Tell the driver you will alight at Bauang-Caba Boundary Arch./You can walk or take a motorcycle to Lapuz Grape Farm./Alternatively, if you want to visit Lomboy Farm, the pioneer in grape farm in La Union, It’s just along the way of National Highway in Bauang.', 'March to May is the best time as it is Grape Picking Season.', 'Picture taking/Eating fresh grapes/Experience picking up fresh grapes from the Farm'),
(4, 4, 'Ride a bus to Laoag and ride another bus to Pagudpod or Cagayan bound bus and alight at the Kapurpurawan Access Road./Ride a tricycle and you will arrived at the food stores. From the food stores, there\'s a stairs going down and may walk by following the trail or you may rent a horseback ride./Along the trail, the view is eye-catching. Take a look and enjoy the the waves of the Bangui bay. It\'s very relaxing./You may now clearly see the White Rock Formation. Just be careful here because some parts of the rock formation is slippery.', 'It’s best to visit the rock formations during the warm season, which is from November to April. The perfect time for visiting Kapurpurawan is early in the morning.', 'Sightseeing/Picture Taking'),
(5, 5, 'The Northwind Bangui Bay Project is situated at the northwest tip of the island of Luzon, in the municipality of Bangui, Ilocos Norte, Philippines. /If you\'re going to drive from Laoag City, take the Pan-Philippine Highway / AH26. You\'ll be able to see Cape Bojeador and Wind Farm Burgos./After passing the Burgos Wind Farm, turn left for a few metres. Travel straight ahead until you enter Estress Resort, then turn right to arrive at the destination.', 'Bangui Windmill Farm is visited by thousands of tourists, particularly during summer season. There are no costs to pay to get a beautiful shot beneath one of the giant windmills. To get a view of the stunning windmill draw, make sure to visit the windmill farm during the daytime.', 'Sightseeing/Picture Taking'),
(6, 6, 'From Manila, fly to Basco, the capital of Batanes. Diura Beach is easily accessible by tricycle or motorcycle from Basco Airport.', 'The best time to visit is during the fishing season, which is usually from April to June. This will give you the chance to see the dorado hanging outside the cogon houses and the boats docked on the beach.', 'Fishing/Picture Taking/Breathtaking Places to visit'),
(7, 7, 'From Manila, one can take a bus bound for Sta. Ana, tourists can also take a flight going to Tuguegarao./Upon arriving to Sta. Ana, take a tricycle cab going to Sta. Vicente port./From there, you can rent a boat that will take you to Palaui Island./Upon reaching the island, it is just a short trek going to the Lighthouse.', 'Getting to the lighthouse requires a bit of a trek, which can be slippery during the rainy season. To avoid this, visit during the dry season, which is usually from November to May. Avoid going at noon, as the heat from the midday sun can be scorching. ', 'Picture Taking/Sightseeing/Climbing the tower'),
(8, 8, 'Take an air-condition bus (Florida Bus Lines, Baliwag Transit, Victory Liner, etc.) Bound for Cagayan Valley, it passes by the province of Isabela via the Maharlika hi-way and get off at Satiago City./From the City, just take a tricycle to Balay Na Santiago along Miranda Street (near the Barangay hall of Calao West).', 'Summer Vacation and it’s open daily from 8:00AM to 12:00 PM and 1:30 PM to 5:00 PM', 'Picture Taking/Learning the history of items/Appreciation of one’s culture'),
(9, 9, 'From Manila catch a bus to Isabela or Cagayan and get off at Santa Fe, Nueva Vizcaya/From the highway, transfer to a tricycle to Barangay Imugan', 'During summer or Sunny day is the best day to visit, explore and experience the beauty of the falls, it is not advisable to visit to the waterfalls during rainy days.', 'Swimming/Picture Taking/Sightseeing'),
(10, 10, 'Cebu Pacific flies daily to Tuguegarao and Cauayan and from there you can simply take a van to Maddela, Quirino Province. However, if you find flying too expensive, Five Star (Cubao), GV Florida, and Northern Luzon (Sampaloc) bus lines have direct trips to Maddela at 8 PM daily./After getting to Maddela, all there is to do is hop on a tricycle to the Governor’s Rapids and other spots you would like to see nearby.', 'April to May since the water is crystal clear during summer.', 'Kayaking/Fishing/Swimming'),
(11, 11, 'From Manila, it will pass through Dinalungan going to Casiguran. There are bus companies in Manila that have direct trips to Casiguran, You can also do it via Baler, and it’s just a van ride going to Dinalungan.', 'The best time to visit Bulawan in the Philippines is from January through March, June and August through December. In this period you have a warm temperature', 'Picture Taking/Sightseeing/Swimming'),
(12, 12, 'By using the North Luzon Expressway (NLEX) and exiting at San Fernando, Pampanga, go west next on Jose Abad Santos Avenue (Gapan-Olongapo Road) in the direction of Pampanga\'s Bacolor, Guagua, and Lubao./Turn left at Roman Superhighway when you get to Dinalupihan. Turn right at Gov. J.J. Linao National Road once you\'ve reached Balanga City. To get to the town of Bagac, use the picturesque path that runs alongside Mt. Samat. Observe the road signs directing you to Las Casas', 'This is an all-year-round destination and can be visited any time of day.', 'Appreciation of one’s culture/Picture Taking/Breathtaking Places to visit'),
(13, 13, 'From Manila, Bagac, Bataan is a 3-hour drive via the North Luzon Expressway (NLEX) and exit at San Fernando, Pampanga. Take the westbound side of Jose Abad Santos Avenue (Gapan-Olongapo Road), heading towards Bacolor, Guagua, and Lubao in Pampanga/Upon reaching Dinalupihan, turn left at Roman Superhighway. Once in Balanga City, turn right at Gov. J.J. Linao National Road. Drive along the scenic route at the foot of Mt. Samat until you reach the town of Bagac', 'During Sunny days for the better experience.', 'Sightseeing/Picture Taking/Learning the history of the tower'),
(14, 14, 'There is no direct connection from Manila to Mount Pinatubo. However, you can take the train to Cubao LRT, take the walk to Araneta Center Bus Terminal, take the bus to Capas, then take the taxi to Mount Pinatubo. Alternatively, you can take the taxi to Mount Pinatubo.', 'It is best to marvel at and experience the beauty of Mt. Pinatubo on dry and summer season from December to May. While hiking is allowed any time of the year, it\'s not recommended to go during the typhoon months from June to September since heavy rains can cause lahar floods in the area.', 'Picture Taking/Sightseeing'),
(15, 15, 'From Manila, take the North Luzon Expressway, exit Sta. Ines Toll Plaza in Mabalacat, Pampanga. Proceed towards north to Tarlac City./Upon reaching Brgy. San Sebastian (Hon Kee Tea House on your right or Vilmar Restaurant on your left), take a left turn to the bypass road (Tarlac - Pangasinan) towards the town of Camiling./Follow the 36-km backcountry but well-paved road to Brgy. Lubigan in San Jose, Tarlac (turns are well signposted)./The monastery is located at the heart of the 278-ha Tarlac Ecotourism Park in Brgy. Lubigan, San Jose, Tarlac.', 'This is an all-year-round destination and can be visited any time of day.', 'Picture Taking/Breathtaking places to check/Sightseeing');
